==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scotia
<hw>Sco"ti*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>skoti`a</grk> darkness, a sunken molding in the base of a pillar,
so called from the dark shadow it casts, from <grk>sko`tos</grk>
darkness.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A concave molding used
especially in classical architecture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scotia</ent>⟦br⟧

